E. COLI EHEC - JAPAN (02): (SAITAMA) O157, POTATO SALAD
*******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 22 Aug 2017
Source: EpiCore Global Surveillance Project [edited]


According to the Mainichi Shimbun News (https://mainichi.jp/articles/20170823/k00/00m/040/113000c [in Japanese]), _Escherichia coli_ O157 was detected from a total of 10 cases. 6 consumed potato salad that was provided by a supermarket called the Delicious Kagohara. 3 consumed potato salad sold by the Delicious Kumagaya, a supermarket affiliated with Delicious Kagohara. Another case was reported from Maebashi city who consumed potato salad sold by another affiliated supermarket in Maebashi. The potato salad was produced by a food producer located in Takasaki city, Gumma prefecture. The detailed information on the ingredients that might have caused illness is not reported in the news. The 5 year-old girl who developed hemolytic-uremic syndrome (HUS) has [regained consciousness], but is still hospitalized.

--
communicated by:
EpiCore Surveillance Project member
Dr Masaki Ota
Research Institute of Tuberculosis
Tokyo
Japan

